data.title: Best lunch value around
data.text: This place has great food and friendly service. They genuinely seem happy to have you in the restaurant, and it shows. I love the "Dip" French Dip sandwich. Everything is yummy and freshly made. Great bread as well.

data.title: Always good
data.text:
I love it, service was fast at the counter, and the food is always good.  I am a little biased on what is "good" because I always order the same sandwich.. over an over.  The Baja Chicken.
We order from here for lunch work meetings as well.  Always looks good to clients, because in my opinion it is a step up.

data.title: Fast healthy lunch.
data.text: They turn and burn the long line. Food is tasty and reasonably priced. Love their tomato basil soup and half sandwich option. It's really fresh and there are loads of options. Very reasonably priced.

data.title: Great selection great prices and lunch
data.text: If you are short on time and cash, then this is the place for you. There is a great selection  of soups and sandwiches at a great price!

data.title: Narrow and deep sandwiches
data.text: I purchased two sandwiches in their new front in Eagan, MN.  The sandwiches were good, but boring.  Much of the menu is based around grilled chicken or marinated sirloin.  It is to your advantage to go to Subway, where you may get more choices and less sirloin.  FYI, I got the Baja (grilled chicken) and the Longhorn (BBQ marinated sirloin steak).  Better check the menu out before going there!

data.title: Lunchtime good food but lacking customer service
data.text: I haven't been to Crumb in a couple of years so was excited to see what has changed. Food was still good but the customer service was completely missing. Four employees working, all talking amongst themselves in Spanish instead of helping customers. I'm fine with them chatting but wait until you have served customers first

data.title: Tasty & Efficient!
data.text: Food is always excellent a favorite in our office! Even when the line is long it moves fast.don't worry if the line is nearly out the door, they move people through very efficiently.

data.title: Very good local Eden Prairie "Deli"
data.text:
This is good local "Deli" in Eden Prairie. It is a popular luncheon spot because of the soups,  sandwiches, and wraps they make. The foods are made in front of you and over the years I have not had a bad soup, salad or sandwich here. The Beef and Blue is my favorite wrap and the soups (tortilla and tomato bisques) are my favorite. My impression is that they serve quality foods at a reasonable price. I have always found the service helpful and professional. 
For those of you who grew up on the East Coast, like I did, the name Deli has a different meaning to me.This is not the New York Jewish style deli (where I grew up) where you can buy meats, bread and salads by the pound. However, I do frequent this Deli because like the East Coast Deli's they take pride in what they serve.
